description:
A Map by Tagtheatre

&amp;lt;b&amp;gt;YOUNG Co. have successfully reached the second round of an application to take part in &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;http://www.contactingtheworld.org/content/news_on_2008/index.php&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Contacting the World&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, run by &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;http://www.contact-theatre.org/&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Contact Theatre&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, Manchester. If we get through we will be twinned with another company in a different part of the world and collaborate over the internet before coming together in July next year during &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;http://www.liverpool08.com/&amp;quot;&amp;gt;City of Culture&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; in Liverpool. &amp;lt;/b&amp;gt;

We were given the following task:
&amp;lt;b&amp;gt;Next time you meet, go somewhere different collaborate with someone new and report back. 

This map has been created to show the participants in our project and the work we undertook:&amp;lt;/b&amp;gt;
Nine members of YOUNG Co., along with Neil Packham (Community Drama Director) went to &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;http://www.glasgowmuseums.com/venue/index.cfm?venueid=4&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Kelvingrove Art Gallery and Museum&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; where they met up with Polly Smith and Lorraine Maule, who were restoring an oil painting, in one of the galleries. The painting in question was &amp;quot;Glassford Family Portrait&amp;quot; by Archibald McLauchlan (c 1767). 

Both groups introduced themselves, then Polly and Lorraine spoke about the painting, the background, social and historical relevance and their method of restoration.

YOUNG Co. members asked loads of questions and found out about the painting and the restoration process. In the spirit of a new collaboration, the group then swapped roles so that  YOUNG Co. took on the role of the experts, and Polly and Lorraine became the questioning visitors.  This evolved in a very spontaneous manner and both sides took well to their new roles. We felt that this kept true to the Contacting the World task. Eve, one of the YOUNG Co. filmed the event. This footage will be added to the YOUNG Co. page on the TAG website (see link below). 

&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;http://www.tag-theatre.co.uk/index.cfm/page/29&amp;quot;&amp;gt;YOUNG Co. web page&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;

&amp;lt;b&amp;gt;You can browse our map to find out about the people and places involved.&amp;lt;/b&amp;gt;
Each participant has answered a few questions about themselves and provided some pictures. The suggested images were to be of themselves, of something from their home and of their dream destination. Happy browsing!

We hope to be able to develop our mapping for Contacting The World, with YOUNG Co. taking over the reigns!
